<h2 class="bold font-l">"Live and be free..."</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
Expiring from his wounds, Gilbert professes his love to Violet. However, she cries about the meaning of said word and begs Gilbert to tell her about it. </p>
<p class='example_row'>Example of:<br><a href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhatIsThisThingYouCallLove" class='trope-example-link'>What Is This Thing You Call "Love"?</a></p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="wb87fj" data-video-descrip="The letters that Violet and Ann's mother wrote were to be delivered to Ann herself after her mother died. The letters are a memento to assure and encourage her future and decisions." data-video-title="Dear Ann" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/wb87fj_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/wb87fj.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/WriteBackToTheFuture" data-video-tropename="Write Back to the Future" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="LightNovel/VioletEvergarden" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/wb87fj.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">Dear Ann</span></p>
